Configuration and Testing of Firewall and VPN
Aim

To configure and test Firewall and VPN settings in order to ensure secure network communication.

Objectives

To implement firewall rules

To control network traffic

To establish a secure VPN tunnel

To verify encrypted communication

To enhance network security

Theory / Background

A firewall acts as a barrier between trusted and untrusted networks by filtering packets based on predefined rules. VPN (Virtual Private Network) provides encrypted communication over public networks, ensuring confidentiality and integrity. Firewalls and VPNs are essential components of modern network security.

Tools / Software Used

UFW Firewall

OpenVPN

Procedure
Firewall Configuration

Firewall service is enabled.

Rules are added to allow or deny services.

Firewall status is verified.

VPN Configuration

VPN software is installed.

Configuration files are loaded.

Secure tunnel is established.

IP address is verified.

Program / Commands Used
sudo ufw enable
sudo ufw allow ssh
sudo ufw deny 80
sudo ufw status
sudo openvpn client.ovpn

Output

Firewall rules were enforced successfully.

Network traffic was filtered.

VPN connection was established.

Result

Firewall and VPN were successfully configured and tested to provide secure communication.
